        "subtype": "usage",
        "text": "worn cloak",
        "type": "stat_block_section"
      }
    },
    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "This gaudy and extravagant cloak is adorned with brilliant gems and a fur trim. While wearing the cloak, you gain instant fame and notoriety, granting you a +1 item bonus to Diplomacy checks to Make an Impression. Creatures attempting to learn about you gain the same bonus to Gather Information about you.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "legacy",
        "game-id": "67a22784fdff12403013a5af60fb8621",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Enchantment",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "4.0",
              "aonid": 1,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "4.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 631",
              "aonid": 1,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 631",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Core Rulebook",
            "page": 631,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Effects and magic items with this trait are associated with the enchantment school of magic, typically involving mind control, emotion alteration, and other mental effects.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 98,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "56b56ea5f9d865dc549f0ed7372ab504",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "invest",
            "aonid": 2799,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "invest",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Invested",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "GM Core pg. 219",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "GM Core pg. 219",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "GM Core",
            "page": 219,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A character can invest only 10 magical items that have the invested trait. None of the magical effects of the item apply if the character hasn\u2019t invested it, nor can it be activated, though the character still gains any normal benefits from wearing the physical item (like a hat keeping rain off their head).",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Magical",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
